President Obama has signed a disaster declaration for the state of New Jersey, providing federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts after a severe storm on June 23, 2015. The funding will be available for emergency work, facility repairs or replacements, and hazard mitigation measures. Seamus K. Leary has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Further designations may be made in the future based on damage assessments.